If it is true that judges are independent and impartial, it is not the truth they judge, especially in the case of defamation persecutions, but the law.
Unsurprisingly, this fundamental difference is completely hidden by Mr. - Garver.
Why, according to Barrick Gold, would the best way to bring a public debate to harm anyone who dares to hold a position contrary to theirs?
The outcome of the lawsuit is of little importance, the authors and publisher of the book Noir Canada will have to spend considerable sums in order to prepare their defense and fight, with very unequal weapons, against an army of lawyers supported by the miner's almost bottomless pockets.
